Year.definition: this is the year of the season that was played.

name.definition: The full name of the player participating in the season.

position.definition: The player's position on the team, such as Running Back (RB) or Wide Receiver (WR).

team.definition: The abbreviated name of the team the player is associated with, such as ARI for Arizona Cardinals.

adp.definition: Average draft position, indicating the typical position a player is drafted in fantasy leagues.

PlayerID.definition: A unique identifier assigned to each player, often derived from a combination of letters from their name.

Employee_Name.definition: The full name of the employee, presented as 'Last, First M'.

EmpID.definition: A unique identification number assigned to each employee.

MarriedID.definition: A binary indicator where 1 indicates the employee is married and 0 indicates they are not.

MaritalStatusID.definition: A numeric identifier corresponding to the employee's marital status.

GenderID.definition: A numeric identifier corresponding to the employee's gender.

EmpStatusID.definition: A numeric identifier that represents the employment status of the employee.

DeptID.definition: A numeric identifier corresponding to the department the employee belongs to.

PerfScoreID.definition: A numeric identifier representing the performance score or rating of the employee.

FromDiversityJobFairID.definition: A binary indicator where 1 signifies the employee was recruited through a diversity job fair and 0 otherwise.

Salary.definition: The salary of the employee, usually expressed in annual terms.

Termd.definition: A binary indicator showing whether the employee has been terminated (1) or not (0).

PositionID.definition: A numeric identifier corresponding to the position or job title of the employee.

Position.definition: The job title or position held by the employee.

State.definition: The state of residence or work location associated with the employee.

Zip.definition: The ZIP code associated with the employee's residence or work location.

DOB.definition: The date of birth of the employee, usually in MM/DD/YYYY format.

Sex.definition: The gender of the employee, typically recorded as Male, Female, etc.

MaritalDesc.definition: A description of the employee's marital status (e.g., Single, Married, Divorced).

CitizenDesc.definition: A description of the employee's citizenship status (e.g., U.S. Citizen, Non-Citizen, etc.).

HispanicLatino.definition: A binary indicator where 1 signifies that the employee identifies as Hispanic or Latino and 0 otherwise.

RaceDesc.definition: A description of the employee's race or ethnicity.

DateofHire.definition: The date the employee was hired, typically in MM/DD/YYYY format.

DateofTermination.definition: The date the employee was terminated, if applicable, in MM/DD/YYYY format.

TermReason.definition: A description of the reason for the employee's termination, if applicable.

EmploymentStatus.definition: A description of the employee's current employment status (e.g., Active, Terminated, Leave of Absence, etc).

Department.definition: The department within the organization where the employee works.

ManagerName.definition: The full name of the employee's direct manager or supervisor.

ManagerID.definition: A unique identification number assigned to the employee's manager.

RecruitmentSource.definition: A description of how the employee was recruited (e.g., Online, Referral, Job Fair).

PerformanceScore.definition: A description or rating of the employee's performance score.

EngagementSurvey.definition: The score from an engagement survey assessing employee's engagement level, usually on a scale such as 1 to 5.

EmpSatisfaction.definition: The score representing employee satisfaction, often measured on a scale such as 1 to 5.

SpecialProjectsCount.definition: The number of special projects the employee is currently involved in or has completed.

LastPerformanceReview_Date.definition: The date of the last performance review for the employee, typically in MM/DD/YYYY format.

DaysLateLast30.definition: The number of days the employee was late to work over the last 30 days.

Absences.definition: The number of days the employee was absent from work.

position.definition: Position played by the player (e.g., WR for Wide Receiver).

season_type.definition: Type of season (e.g., regular season, playoffs).

opponent_team.definition: The team the player's team is competing against.

completions.definition: Number of completed passes by the player.

attempts.definition: Number of passing attempts made by the player.

passing_yards.definition: Total yards gained by the player through passing.

passing_tds.definition: Touchdowns scored by the player through passing.

interceptions.definition: Total number of interceptions thrown by the player.

sacks.definition: Number of times the player was sacked.

sack_yards.definition: Total yards lost due to sacks.

sack_fumbles.definition: Fumbles lost by the player as a result of being sacked.

sack_fumbles_lost.definition: Number of sack-based fumbles lost by the player.

passing_air_yards.definition: Total yards the ball traveled in the air before being caught during passing plays.

passing_yards_after_catch.definition: Total yards gained by receiving players after the catch during passing plays.

passing_first_downs.definition: Number of first downs achieved by passing.

passing_2pt_conversions.definition: Number of successful two-point conversions completed by the player by passing.

carries.definition: Number of rushing plays made by the player.

rushing_yards.definition: Total yards gained through rushing plays.

rushing_fumbles.definition: Number of occasions the player fumbled the ball during a rushing play.

rushing_fumbles_lost.definition: Fumbles lost by the player during rushing plays.

rushing_first_downs.definition: Number of first downs achieved by the player through rushing.

rushing_2pt_conversions.definition: Number of successful two-point conversions achieved by rushing.

receptions.definition: Number of catches made by the player.

targets.definition: Number of times the player was targeted with a pass.

receiving_yards.definition: Total yards gained through catching passes.

receiving_fumbles.definition: Number of fumbles made by the player during receptions.

receiving_fumbles_lost.definition: Number of fumbles lost by the player during receptions.

receiving_air_yards.definition: Total distance the ball traveled in the air to the player on receptions.

receiving_yards_after_catch.definition: Total additional yards gained by the player after making a reception.

receiving_first_downs.definition: Number of first downs achieved via receptions.

receiving_2pt_conversions.definition: Number of successful two-point conversions achieved through receptions.

target_share.definition: Proportion of team passes in which player was targeted.

air_yards_share.definition: Proportion of total air yards of the team attributed to the player.

fantasy_points.definition: Fantasy points scored by the player based on performance metrics.

fantasy_points_ppr.definition: Fantasy points scored under point-per-reception format.

total_yards.definition: Sum of all yards gained through passing, rushing, and receiving.

ypa.definition: Average yards gained per passing attempt by the player.

ypc.definition: Average yards gained per carry during rushing plays.

touches.definition: Total number of carries and receptions by the player.

count.definition: A generic counter for performance or occurrences specific to context.

pass_td_percentage.definition: Percentage of passing attempts resulting in touchdowns.

rush_td_percentage.definition: Percentage of rushing attempts resulting in touchdowns.

rec_td_percentage.definition: Percentage of receptions resulting in touchdowns.

total_tds.definition: Total number of touchdowns scored by the player.

td_percentage.definition: Overall percentage of plays resulting in touchdowns.

passer_rating.definition: Quarterback rating based on performance metrics.

rookie_season.definition: Indicator of whether it is the player's first season.

college.definition: Name of the college the player attended.

birth_date.definition: Date of birth of the player.

rookie_age.definition: Age of the player during their rookie season.

height_cm.definition: Height of the player in centimeters.

height_ft.definition: Height of the player in feet.

round.definition: Draft round in which the player was selected.

overall.definition: Overall pick number in the draft.

forty.definition: Time taken by the player to run 40-yard dash.

bench.definition: Number of repetitions of bench presses completed by the player.

vertical.definition: Vertical leap height of the player.

index.definition: An index or ranking based on specific criteria.

offense_snaps.definition: Number of offensive plays the player participated in.

teams_offense_snaps.definition: Total offensive snaps played by the team.

offense_pct.definition: Percentage of team offensive plays player participated in.

years_played.definition: Total number of years the player has played professionally.
